{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "This fixes issue #20\r\n\r\nMy solution is to direct all logging output into a directory called `tmp-ign` and then delete `tmp-ign` at the end of each set of tests that use it. Most of the tests use the `AutoLogFixture`, so putting the cleanup in that class's destructor solved most of the problem cases.\r\n\r\nI decided to make the `tmp-ign` a visible directory (as opposed to making it something like `.tmp-ign`) to make it more noticeable for us to debug or cleanup if it fails to be removed at the end of any tests.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>This fixes issue <a href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-common/issues/20/console_test-creates-a-bunch-of-garbage\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Console_TEST creates a bunch of garbage directories in the home directory\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#20</s></a></p>\n<p>My solution is to direct all logging output into a directory called <code>tmp-ign</code> and then delete <code>tmp-ign</code> at the end of each set of tests that use it. Most of the tests use the <code>AutoLogFixture</code>, so putting the cleanup in that class's destructor solved most of the problem cases.</p>\n<p>I decided to make the <code>tmp-ign</code> a visible directory (as opposed to making it something like <code>.tmp-ign</code>) to make it more noticeable for us to debug or cleanup if it fails to be removed at the end of any tests.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Cleanup log directories after tests are run", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Cleanup log directories after tests are run</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "This fixes issue #20\r\n\r\nMy solution is to direct all logging output into a directory called `tmp-ign` and then delete `tmp-ign` at the end of each set of tests that use it. Most of the tests use the `AutoLogFixture`, so putting the cleanup in that class's destructor solved most of the problem cases.\r\n\r\nI decided to make the `tmp-ign` a visible direct